      <bioghist id="aspace_7a4d2c994e56d19bfc8df92e7696b3bb">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>William Sloane Coffin, Sr. (1879-1933) was a graduate of the Yale College Class of 1900. He later worked as an executive in his family's business, the W. &amp; J. Sloane Company, and was president of the Metropolitan Museum of Art. He is the father of noted Christian minister and peace activist, William Sloane Coffin, Jr.</p>  
      </bioghist>
